<h3 id="homebrew-">Homebrew <a id="section2-2"></a></h3>

<p>After the command line tools suite has completed installation, return to your command line window and enter the following to install <a href="http://brew.sh/">Homebrew</a>:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><pre class="highlight"><code>/usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"
</code></pre>
</div>

<p>You’ll need to press enter when prompted and enter your computer password when asked. For reference, below is a screenshot of the command entered into the author’s command line, followed by all the text that appeared (including the prompt to press enter, and to enter my password).</p>

<!--figure tags without plugin: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/19331362/using-an-image-caption-in-markdown-jekyll -->

